race.comment: LEKTRA DAMIAN (1) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (22.46) at Warrnambool behind Little Narla in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. The form out of his last race has been franked. Can measure up this time. RED TO BURN (2) trailed the lead and fought on well to be beaten a nose into second (23.45) at this track in a Other over 400m. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Hard to beat again. DELL MISTER (4) comes off an average effort last start when fifth at this track over 400m behind Wind Whiskers (23.87) in a Grade 4/5. Was in the money the start prior. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Shapes as one to consider. CHEQUES TO BURN (5) is worth another chance despite missing the top-three here most recently. Something for the Multiples: LITTLEFOOT (9)
